#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:-1
msgid ""
"Learn about the Lua build system in Spack for packages using rockspec files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:14
msgid "Lua"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:16
msgid ""
"The ``Lua`` build system is a helper for the common case of Lua packages "
"that provide a rockspec file. This is not meant to take a rock archive, but "
"to build a source archive or repository that provides a rockspec, which "
"should cover most Lua packages. In the case a Lua package builds by Make "
"rather than LuaRocks, prefer MakefilePackage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:21
msgid "Phases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:23
msgid ""
"The ``LuaBuilder`` and ``LuaPackage`` base classes come with the following "
"phases:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:25
msgid ""
"``unpack`` - if using a rock, unpacks the rock and moves into the source "
"directory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:26
msgid "``preprocess`` - adjust sources or rockspec to fix build"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:27
msgid "``install`` - install the project"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:29
msgid "By default, these phases run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:31
msgid ""
"# If the archive is a source rock\n"
"$ luarocks unpack <archive>.src.rock\n"
"$ # preprocess is a no-op by default\n"
"$ luarocks make <name>.rockspec"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:39
msgid "Any of these phases can be overridden in your package as necessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:42
msgid "Important files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:44
msgid ""
"Packages that use the Lua/LuaRocks build system can be identified by the "
"presence of a ``*.rockspec`` file in their source tree, or can be fetched as "
"a source rock archive (``.src.rock``). This file declares things like build "
"instructions and dependencies. The ``.src.rock`` also contains all code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:48
msgid ""
"It is common for the rockspec file to list the Lua version required in a "
"dependency. The LuaPackage class adds appropriate dependencies on a Lua "
"implementation, but it is a good idea to specify the version required with a "
"``depends_on`` statement. The block normally will be a table definition like "
"this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:52
msgid ""
"dependencies = {\n"
"   \"lua >= 5.1\",\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:58
msgid ""
"The LuaPackage class supports source repositories and archives containing a "
"rockspec and directly downloading source rock files. It *does not* support "
"downloading dependencies listed inside a rockspec, and thus does not support "
"directly downloading a rockspec as an archive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:62
msgid "Build system dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:64
msgid ""
"All base dependencies are added by the build system, but LuaRocks is run to "
"avoid downloading extra Lua dependencies during build. If the package needs "
"Lua libraries outside the standard set, they should be added as dependencies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:67
msgid ""
"To specify a Lua version constraint but allow all Lua implementations, "
"prefer to use ``depends_on(\"lua-lang@5.1:5.1.99\")`` to express any 5.1 "
"compatible version. If the package requires LuaJit rather than Lua, a "
"``depends_on(\"luajit\")`` should be used to ensure a LuaJit distribution is "
"used instead of the Lua interpreter. Alternately, if only interpreted Lua "
"will work, ``depends_on(\"lua\")`` will express that."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:72
msgid "Passing arguments to luarocks make"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:74
msgid ""
"If you need to pass any arguments to the ``luarocks make`` call, you can "
"override the ``luarocks_args`` method like so:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:76
msgid ""
"def luarocks_args(self):\n"
"    return [\"flag1\", \"flag2\"]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:81
msgid ""
"One common use of this is to override warnings or flags for newer compilers, "
"as in:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:83
msgid ""
"def luarocks_args(self):\n"
"    return [\"CFLAGS='-Wno-error=implicit-function-declaration'\"]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:89
msgid "External documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../build_systems/luapackage.rst:91
msgid ""
"For more information on the LuaRocks build system, see: https://luarocks.org/"
msgstr ""
